---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Board Advisory for SI & IT Services';
const description = 'Board-level advisory helping system integrators and IT services firms set agentic AI strategy, governance, and a credible offering.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="py-12 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Board Advisory for SI &amp; IT Services Firms</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Agentic AI is reshaping the IT services market faster than most leadership teams are prepared for. I work at board level with system integrators and IT services firms to turn that disruption into strategy, offering, and competitive advantage — drawing on building <a href="https://meetloyd.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">MeetLoyd</a> and on standards work at the UN ITU (SG17).
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Where I help</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Agentic strategy</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Board-level briefings on the agentic shift</li>
              <li>• Threat &amp; opportunity mapping for your services portfolio</li>
              <li>• Where agents disrupt, and where they create margin</li>
              <li>• 3-year strategic narrative for the board and investors</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Building an agentic offering</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Designing a credible agentic services line</li>
              <li>• Packaging, pricing, and outcome-based models</li>
              <li>• Go-to-market and positioning vs. the field</li>
              <li>• Partner &amp; platform strategy (make vs. buy)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Governance &amp; risk</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Agentic AI governance and operating guardrails</li>
              <li>• EU AI Act, security, and trustworthy agent identity</li>
              <li>• Risk posture clients and regulators will accept</li>
              <li>• Informed by UN ITU SG17 standards work</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Operating model &amp; enablement</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Reskilling delivery teams for agent-led work</li>
              <li>• Margins and utilization in an agentic delivery model</li>
              <li>• Executive and practice-lead enablement</li>
              <li>• Internal adoption to dogfood your own offering</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Who I work with</h2>
        <p>System integrators, IT services firms, and consultancies — and the regulated, high-trust enterprises they serve (financial services, healthcare, public sector, and companies facing EU AI Act obligations).</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Engagement models</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-600 pl-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Board briefing / workshop</h3>
            <p class="text-sm">A focused session to align the board and executive team on the agentic shift and its implications for the firm.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-600 pl-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Strategy sprint (2-6 weeks)</h3>
            <p class="text-sm">Deep-dive on agentic strategy, offering design, or governance, with a board-ready deliverable.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-600 pl-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Ongoing board advisor</h3>
            <p class="text-sm">Recurring board-level advisory through the transition — quarterly cadence or fractional engagement.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-600 pl-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Due diligence</h3>
            <p class="text-sm">Assessing agentic capability and risk for buy-side or sell-side transactions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Preparing your firm for the agentic era?</h3>
          <p class="mb-4">Let's discuss how to turn the agentic shift into your firm's advantage — at board level.</p>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/beaumois/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-white text-blue-600 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors">
            Let's discuss on LinkedIn
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
